Subject: [sfraves] BSP: Faktion & THIRSTY 6-27 a tale of two club nights- plus Radio
 Integrated live!

You can call Faktion and Thirsty, two awesome techno clubs virtually 
across the street from each other, a battle royale of techno, tech-house 
and progressive or you can call it a 6th & Mission techno-house club 
love affair... But one thing you can definitely call it is an easy way 
to club hop and get a sense of the reason why techno is surely blowing 
up in SF.

On one side of the street you have Faktion poppin' at ANU, a dope little 
techno club that is slowly gaining a decent following of people (that 
actually aren't *only* DJs and promoters), with an extra dope line up:

Saya:: ] Faktion | BABD [
Toro Toro::  ] Faktion | FnF [
DJ Disconnect:: ] Faktion | DEF| Radio Integrated [

.....and on the other side of the street you have Thirsty at Matador, a 
club with hope, heart some serious skills to back it up, and a damned 
decent talent pool to boot:

Amber:: ] Sister SF | iamthedj.com [
Denise:: ] Mizumo Music | djdenise.com [
Missao:: ] Source4 | Thirsty [
Chel-C Faith LIVE PA:: ] DEF | Radio Integrated [

OK, so you're not in SF? Don't want to come out of your wired cave of 
Internet bliss? No problem! We will just have to bring the party to you. 
Radio Integrated will be broadcasting live from Faktion all night and 
recording all the sets from Thirsty for a later air date. This will be 
your last chance to catch Radio Integrated live for a solid month while 
we prepare to overhaul the http://www.defsf.com site and bring you a 24 
hour broadcast day on DEF's Radio Integrated.

please find details below:
http://www.defsf.com/radiointegrated/integrated or subscribe to the 
links below at the footer of this message.

Tune in to Radio Integrated, broadcasting live from Faktion from 
10pm-2am Pacific this Friday night at::

http://radio.defsf.com:1200

peace, love, respect
sean

DEF

Subject: [sfraves] bsp: geekout presentation on algorithmic dance music 7/29

A while ago I came on here bragging about my robot rock:

http://www.vimeo.com/947877
http://gilesbowkett.blogspot.com/2008/05/archaeopteryx-ambient-evil-robot-army.html

I'll be up in SF on a Tuesday next month explaining how it works to a
meetup of geek musicians and music geeks. It'll be a code- and
tech-centric presentation, and you'll get the most out of it if you
understand some basic technical details of Ruby, MIDI, Reason, Live,
and/or classic old-school step sequencers. (Although if you understand
Python but not Ruby, that's easily close enough to get the gist.)

Was going to do this earlier in June but got sick. Assuming I actually
do it this time, I'll post the details nearer the time of the actual
event.

-- 

Giles Soundwave/Goat Boy/Bowkett
http://www.gilesgoatboy.org/
http://gilesbowkett.blogspot.com (code)

Subject: [sfraves] ::BSP:: Tonight's the night! Faktion! Thirsty! 6th Street techno block party!


Continuing our tradition of bringing uniquely amazing talent, this month
Faktion brings a rarely heard group of local headliners to the deck.  We've
got Friends&Family favorite TORO TORO this month, along with the Bliss
Factory's legendary DISCONNECT, and a farewell performance from SAYAKA
as she returns to her native Japan for an indefinite hiatus.  We can't
recall if these 3 towers of turntable (and other gear) talent have ever
played together before, and more importantly it's not clear if we'll
ever get the chance to have them together again, so this will be another
party not to miss!  Once again, VJ sensations HEROIC ROBOT return to
transform this from mere club party to the stuff of legends!

To reiterate how techno is now thriving in San Francisco, 6th Street
has become something of a techno block party!  Right across the street
at Matador (formerly Arrow Bar) bangs Thirsty, with a darn talented group
of lovely folks also worth checking out: Amber (SisterSF|iamthedj.com),
Denise(Mizumo Music|djdenise.com), Missao(Source4|Thirsty), and a LIVE
PA from Chel-C Faith(DEF|RadioIntegrated).  Faktion allows full in/out
privs so you can check out multiple parties without figuring out how
to get from one to the next (just watch out for traffic!)

After your pregaming and happy hour prepartying at Killswitch, we'll
see you at 6th Street tonight!


Friday, 27 June 2008

RAY presents: 

F A K T I O N : because san francisco needs another techno cult

Friday, 27 June 2008:
DISCONNECT: DEF/blissfactory [ Oakland ]
TORO TORO: friends&family/faktion [ SF|Oakland ]
and a special farewell performace by
SAYAKA: BABD/Faktion [ Japan|SF ]
Unbelievably Amazing Visuals by HEROIC ROBOT [ SF ]

Last Fridays @ Anu

DISCONNECT: Disconnect is a techno DJ currently based out of Oakland who
spins a dreamy, groovin' laid back style with a dash of progressive and
Neo Detroit thrown in.  He has been throwing underground parties with the
DEF crew since 2003, and is known for his depth and breadth of knowledge
of all things techno.

TORO TORO: Unorthodox, brilliant and just plain kickass, Toro Toro's
original style and track selection shows his industrial influence, yet
remains true to the principles of modern minimal, and the better examples
of electro house.  Known for his versatility in the underground scene,
we're proud to welcome him as a DJ in residence.

and a special farewell performace by
SAYAKA: Sayaka has been a San Francisco resident since 2004, known not only
here but around the world for her consistent mastery of many genres of
electronic music, including the always difficult downtempo.  She hosted her
own weekly techno event at Olive Bar, but decided to focus on her DJing,
spinning melodic techno with flawless track selection and natural progression.
Having been booked repeatedly in New York, Tokyo and other venues around
the world, we wish her the best in her return to Japan.  Don't miss this
last chance to appreciate how easy she makes it look(it really isn't).


Anu-Bar 
43 Sixth St., San Francisco, CA
10 PM to 2 AM 21+
Cost: $5, free b4 11pm, females free b4 midnight

Official Site: http://www.faktionsf.com/

 
///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

Other parties of interest:
Our friends at KILLSWITCH continue their weekly Friday happy hour techno
set of goodness at UndergroundSF (424 Haight at Webster), 6-10pm.  Prior
to this month's FAKTION, in addition to residents DCOY and JAV8, they've
got our good friends KENNETH SCOTT and TRAVIS DALTAON of Binary and
On!Science.  For July, they've got some other great local talent well
worth having a couple drinks to check out:
THURSDAY, July 3rd: (No KS on July 4th) Dave Aju (Circus Company), Monty Luke (XLR8R,Mothership)
July 11th: Worthy (Dirtybird), Jason Kendig (Honey Soundsystem)
July 18th: KSX2 Extended hours til 2am w/ Roman Stange (Auralism), Emilio Orlandi (Mouth to Mouth), Mossmoss ( Nightlight, Racecar), J_Moody (Meiotic), TomKat (Bassaholics)
July 25th: Mozaic (Raindance, Hookerz & Blow), J.Rogers (Blipswitch) no cover.  

On July 3rd, supperclub, NextAid and Stap[e are hosting a benefit for
NextAid, creating sustainable solutions for children orphaned by AIDS
in Africa.  The lineup alone should convince you: Solar [Sunset], Late
Night Sneaky (Live), Alland Byallo [Kontrol], Monty Luke [Mothership],
Laird [GoldenGateRecordings], J Phlip [Dirtybird], Amber [iamthedj.com],
and Stap[e residents Fil Latorre and Javaight.  Combined with such a
worthy cause, why wouldn't you want to be there?  For more info hit up
www.nextaid.org or myspace/fillatorre.  $10 w/rsvp to events@nextaid.org.

On July 5th, [KONTROL] once again brings some of the biggest and best in
Techno with MICHAEL STAVOSTRAND and one of our personal faves, BUTANE.
10pm-6am, $15 after 11.



///////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////
 
Coming up: Faktion: Last Fridays @ Anu 
Friday, 25 July 2008:
JAK: SubSensory/Akashik/LeftCoastTechno [ Portland|Chile ]
ALLAND BYALLO: Kontrol/Nightlight [ SF|LA ]

I thought I'd let all my friends on SFR know about a little party that Acid
Totem is throwing on Friday 7/11.  The party is located at an oceanfront
campground with incredible views of the Golden Gate, SF, and the Pacific.
Some of you familiar with the area, can probably figure it out.  We've got
all the campsites reserved, which means PARTAY!  We've also got Mozaic
coming out to play as our special guest, so it should be a good one indeed.
To help cover the costs of the party, we are asking for a menial $8.
Presales can be purchased via paypal at  www.acidtotem.net    Camping is
also available on Thursday night at no extra charge, but there will only be
music on Friday night.  To get all the info, visit our website!

Here's a few teaser pix of the location:
http://www.flickr.com/photos/26215800@N04/sets/72157605274746702/



Fri.  7/11
Golden Gate Grooves

Mozaic
Flook
Aleks
5-MeO
Ben haus
Kris Kent
Unityvybe

9p - 6am
www.acidtotem.net
